  "description": [
    "THE UNION JOURNALS Editorial Page Friday October 141960 Editor Backs Kennedy QNE OF THE NATIONS outstanding V magazines is Harpers It is edited by the highlyrespected John Fischer In this months issue Editor Fischer an nounced that he will vote for Sen John F Kennedy for president Fischer cited four compelling rea sons for choosing Kennedy First he noted that the next Congress will almost cer tainly be Democratic and and conse quently a Democratic President becomes highly desirable The coming Administration will have to deal with the worst series of crises since Lincoln Fischer wrote It will need to move fast and decisively and this is only possible when both branches of the government are in the same hands Fischers second reason was that Ken nedy will be in a better position than Nixon to act promptly and with imagina tion Nixon cannot repudiate complete ly the policies of the Eisenhower Adminis tration he stated nor can he ignore the men who provide the financing and the organizational backbone of his party With a few exceptions these are backwardlooking men Joe Pew and George Humphrey types who dread any change and yield to its reluctantly and with suspicion Fischer"
  ],
